# Installation 
### Prequisites:
i) Unity Hub must be installed
ii) Unity 6 must be installed (this can be done by following the instructions on the Unity hub or by following this online tutorial: https://learn.unity.com/pathway/junior-programmer/unit/player-control/tutorial/install-unity-software?version=6.0)
When choosing which version of Unity 6 to install, select 6000.3.1.10f1
iii) Git must be setup on your device or Github Desktop should be installed. In each case, you must sign into Github

### Instructions:
i) Clone the SPELLSTACK repo by running git clone https://github.com/rhatos/Spellstack.git in your terminal or using the link in Github Desktop
ii) Open the Unity Hub and navigate to the location where the SPELLSTACK repo has been cloned
iii) Open the project. It may take some time to compile all of the assets and scripts

# Running the Game
i) Press on the play button icon above the scene and game view

# Implementation
## Tutorials
The Audion Manager system was implemented using a tutorial by Brackeys (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6OT43pvUyfY)
## Gen AI
- Gemini was used for some asset generation of spell combos, such as burning vines, bog trap, mudslide, vine cyclone and steam explosion.
- Gemini was also used for generating code to move between the main menu, story overview and instruction screen
## Ourselves
We sourced 2d assets for most spells and character/mob sprites from itch.io. In some instances, these assets were adjusted to fit the game's aesthetic using Libresprite.
We sourced sounds from pixabay and storyblock. In addition, we created some 8-bit sounds using bfxr.
The music was created using Reaper DAW. The built-in synthesisers were used.
Aside from the aforementioned AI-generated code, we created the codebase with minor assistance from AI for small changes.

